# Rule 07 — Naming Conventions

Applies to all new files from approval forward. **Legacy names stay as-is
unless a file is already being edited for other reasons.** Retroactive
rename campaigns are forbidden — they produce churn, blame-history noise,
and merge conflicts without product value.

This rule codifies the naming conventions already established by
Phases 3A–3K + 4A.1–4B.2 + VS1 Chunks A–B. It does not introduce new
concepts; it freezes existing practice so future code follows the
same shapes.

---

## §1 Packages and folders

**Domain-first, behavior-second.** Every feature lives under its
domain root, with sub-folders per layer-behavior.

```
<domain>/<resource>/<behavior>/
```

- **Domain roots:** `clinical`, `identity`, `tenancy`, `platform`,
  `architecture` (tests only)
- **Behaviors:** `read`, `write`, `api`, `persistence`, `model`,
  `service`, `context`, `fhir`
- **Platform substrate:** `platform/<capability>/` — e.g.
  `platform/audit`, `platform/read`, `platform/write`,
  `platform/security`, `platform/observability`, `platform/persistence`

**Example (Phase 4A.2–4B.2):**
```
clinical/
  patient/
    api/            — PatientController, PatientDtos, PatientFhirController
    read/           — GetPatient*, ListPatients*
    write/          — CreatePatient*, UpdatePatientDemographics*,
                      AddPatientIdentifier*, RevokePatientIdentifier*,
                      PatientSnapshot, Patchable, PatientWriteConfig
    persistence/    — PatientEntity, PatientRepository
    model/          — AdministrativeSex, MrnSource, PatientStatus
    fhir/           — FhirPatient, PatientFhirMapper
```

**Rule:** never mix behaviors in one package. `patient/read/CreatePatientHandler.kt`
is wrong even if it would compile — Create belongs in `write/`.

