## §2 Backend class suffixes (Kotlin)

Every concrete role has a specific suffix. One class, one role.

| Suffix | Role | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `*Command` | Immutable input data class for a handler | `CreatePatientCommand`, `ListPatientsCommand`, `GetPatientCommand` |
| `*Handler` | Business logic; runs inside WriteGate / ReadGate tx | `CreatePatientHandler`, `GetPatientHandler` |
| `*Policy` | Authorization gate; throws `WriteAuthorizationException` on denial | `CreatePatientPolicy`, `ListPatientsPolicy` |
| `*Validator` | Domain-level field validation (post-DTO binding) | `CreatePatientValidator`, `AddPatientIdentifierValidator` |
| `*Auditor` | Emits audit rows on success + denial | `CreatePatientAuditor`, `ListPatientsAuditor` |
| `*Snapshot` | Immutable DB-projection shape returned by handlers | `PatientSnapshot`, `MembershipSnapshot`, `TenantSnapshot` |
| `*Result` | Handler return type when Snapshot is insufficient (paginated pages, paired data) | `ListPatientsResult`, `TenantMembershipResult` |
| `*Request` | HTTP request DTO bound by Spring MVC `@RequestBody` | `CreatePatientRequest`, `InviteMembershipRequest` |
| `*Response` | HTTP response DTO (always wrapped in `ApiResponse<T>` envelope) | `PatientResponse`, `PatientListResponse`, `MembershipResponse` |
| `*Config` | Spring `@Configuration` class | `PatientWriteConfig`, `FlywayDataSourceConfig` |
| `*Gate`, `*Hook`, `*Filter` | Platform substrate | `WriteGate`, `ReadGate`, `PhiRlsTxHook`, `TenantContextFilter` |
| `*Repository` | Spring Data JPA interface | `PatientRepository`, `TenantMembershipRepository` |
| `*Entity` | JPA entity class (NOT a `data class`) | `PatientEntity`, `TenantEntity` |
| `*Exception` | Throwable | `WriteValidationException`, `PreconditionRequiredException` |

**Command-set convention.** For each command name, the full stack is
named identically: `<Verb><Resource>{Command, Handler, Policy, Validator,
Auditor}`. Missing files are OK (reads typically have no Validator);
extra files are not.

