## §4 Authorities (`MedcoreAuthority` enum)

Format: `RESOURCE_ACTION`, both uppercase, singular resource noun,
imperative verb.

✅ `PATIENT_READ`, `PATIENT_CREATE`, `PATIENT_UPDATE`, `MEMBERSHIP_INVITE`,
   `MEMBERSHIP_ROLE_UPDATE`, `MEMBERSHIP_REVOKE`
❌ `READ_PATIENT` (verb-first)
❌ `PATIENTS_READ` (plural resource)
❌ `PATIENT_CAN_READ` (modal qualifier)

---

## §5 Audit actions (`AuditAction` enum)

**Two parallel forms must match.** Java enum in `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`,
persisted `code` in `dot.separated.lowercase`.

| Enum name | Wire `code` |
|---|---|
| `IDENTITY_USER_PROVISIONED` | `identity.user.provisioned` |
| `TENANCY_MEMBERSHIP_INVITED` | `tenancy.membership.invited` |
| `CLINICAL_PATIENT_ACCESSED` | `clinical.patient.accessed` |
| `CLINICAL_PATIENT_LIST_ACCESSED` | `clinical.patient.list_accessed` |
| `AUTHZ_READ_DENIED` | `authz.read.denied` |

Prefix families are **closed**: `identity`, `tenancy`, `clinical`,
`authz`, `audit.chain`. New families require an ADR. Wire codes are a
**stable audit contract** — rename = breaking change = superseding
ADR, never in-place.

---

## §6 Reason slugs (audit `reason` column)

Format: pipe-delimited tokens. First token is always
`intent:<domain>.<resource>.<action>`. Additional tokens are `key:value`,
all **closed-enum or bounded integer**, never free text.

```
intent:clinical.patient.create|mrn_source:GENERATED
intent:clinical.patient.update_demographics|fields:nameGiven,nameFamily
intent:clinical.patient.list|count:3|limit:20|offset:0
intent:tenancy.membership.update_role|from:OWNER|to:ADMIN
intent:clinical.patient.access|denial:INSUFFICIENT_AUTHORITY
```

**Never in a reason:** patient names, MRNs, emails, phone numbers,
free-text comments, exception messages, IP addresses, or anything not
drawn from a closed enum or bounded integer. The audit envelope is
deliberately flat (ADR-003 §3) and dynamic-but-bounded data lives in
these tokens.

