## §7 Flyway migrations

- **Filename:** `V<N>__<snake_case_description>.sql`
- **Placement:** `apps/api/src/main/resources/db/migration/<domain>/`
  where `<domain>` ∈ {`identity`, `tenancy`, `audit`, `clinical`, `flyway`}
- `N` is project-wide monotonic. Domain folders organize by *owner*,
  not by number — migrations from different domains can interleave.
- `__` (double underscore) separates version from description; the
  description uses single underscores.

---

## §8 Tests

| Suffix | Role |
|---|---|
| `*Test.kt` | Unit test (mocks collaborators, no Spring context) |
| `*IntegrationTest.kt` | Integration test (`@SpringBootTest` + Testcontainers) |
| `*LogPhiLeakageTest.kt` | Rule 01 control — PHI must never appear in stdout |
| `*RlsTest.kt` | Row-Level Security enforcement proof |
| `*ArchTest.kt` | ArchUnit architectural invariant |
| `*ConcurrencyTest.kt` | Race / optimistic-concurrency proof |

Frontend tests: `*.test.tsx` for components, `*.test.ts` for modules,
colocated with the subject under test.

---

## §9 Commit messages (Conventional Commits)

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` (Angular-style).

- **type** ∈ {`feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `governance`, `chore`, `refactor`}
- **scope** ∈ {`clinical`, `tenancy`, `identity`, `platform`, `persistence`,
  `web`, `audit`, `adr`, `runbook`}
- **subject**: lowercase, imperative, no trailing period.
- Optional phase tag in parentheses: `(4B.1)`, `(4A.5)`, `(VS1)`.

Examples from history:
- `feat(clinical): first real PHI write path — patient create + update (4A.2)`
- `fix(platform): wire @Primary + @FlywayDataSource DataSource pair so make api-dev starts`
- `docs(runbook): pin stable subject + post-1900 birth dates for VS1 demo seed`

---

## §10 Enforcement posture

- **Forward-only.** This rule ships *after* VS1 Chunk B. Every file
  created from this point forward MUST comply.
- **Opportunistic backfill.** When a file is already being edited for
  other reasons, bring it into compliance in the same diff. Don't open
  separate rename PRs.
- **No retroactive sweeps.** Do not open a PR titled "rename X for
  consistency" unless the rename is load-bearing for a real feature or
  bug fix.
- **Naming drift is a review finding, not a blocker.** Reviewers call
  out violations as optional-fix unless the non-compliant name is
  actively misleading or conflicts with an existing name.

